Some times the resolution error is an indication you aren't doing what you thought. As with mirror its a tool to stop people from hitting their fingers - or to make it clear when they intend to. Kind of a mute point here as the class doesn't have scope beyond the .cc file, but from the Doxygen view of the code perhaps its relevant.

